6. Developer Instructions (Prompt for Claude)
Copy and paste the following block directly to Claude to initiate the development phase.

System Context:
You are an expert Full-Stack Software Engineer and QA Automation Specialist. We are building a platform called "OppoProfile". It is an AI-driven framework that interfaces with the web-based board game Azul (hosted at https://buddyboardgames.com/azul).

Your immediate objectives for Phase 1 are:

1. Understand the Rules of Azul:
Before writing any code, search your knowledge base to fully understand the rules, scoring mechanics, and progression of the board game Azul. You must understand how tiles are drafted from factories, placed on pattern lines, moved to the wall, and how floor penalties work.

2. Explore and Map the Platform (Playwright):
Write a Python script utilizing playwright to navigate to a sample room (e.g., https://buddyboardgames.com/azul?room=MTIzNjc4).

Your script needs to map the UI elements of this specific platform to your understanding of the Azul rules.

Identify the CSS selectors or XPath for: the factories, the center pool, the player boards, the pattern lines, the wall, the floor line, and the score indicators.

Write a function that extracts these UI elements and parses them into a clean, machine-readable JSON object representing the exact current game_state.

3. Action Execution Automation:
Write a corresponding Playwright function execute_move(game_state, action) that takes a programmatic decision (e.g., "Take all red tiles from factory 2 and place them on pattern line 3") and executes the required mouse clicks on the web UI to perform that move.

Please output your understanding of the Azul rules briefly, followed by the proposed JSON state structure, and finally the Playwright Python code to scrape the state and execute a move.